author: Graeme Campbell
title: Dior Homme and Sennheiser Unveil State-of-the-Art Audio Equipment
text:
Visit the original post to see all 9 images from this gallery. 
Two heavyweights of their respective worlds, luxury fashion house Dior Homme and German electronics company Sennheiser, have come together for a state-of-the-art audio equipment collection.
The pair has created a series of red and black products that can be utilized at home or on the move. For kicking back at the pad, an amplifier and various types of headphones are packaged in a slick metal box, while additional Bluetooth headphones come sheathed in either a calfskin storage clutch or backpack for scuff-free use on the go. For those looking to move a little lighter, yet another set of Bluetooth earphones are included, housed in a leather cover.
The collection arrives at select Dior Homme boutiques and Sennheiser stores worldwide at some point this spring. Look out for pricing news in the coming days.
